title: Respond to a data protection request

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content: Under data protection law, anyone can ask if your organisation holds personal information about them - you must respond to their request as soon as possible, and within one month at most.
chunks.plain_content:
Respond to a data protection request
Under data protection law, anyone can ask if your organisation holds personal information about them - you must respond to their request as soon as possible, and within one month at most.

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content: Requests for personal data should be provided for free in most cases.
chunks.plain_content:
Respond to a data protection request
Requests for personal data should be provided for free in most cases.

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content:
Individuals have the right to know:

  • what information is being used
  • why its being used
  • where it came from
  • who can see the information

You must provide:

  • confirmation that you are processing their personal data
  • a copy of that data
  • details of how that data is collected, used and disposed of

You should send them a hard copy - such as a printout or photocopy. If you received the request by email, you can send the information by email if the requester agrees.

Make sure they can understand the information - for example explain what any codes mean. Your response should be:

  • transparent
  • written in clear, plain language
  • in an easily accessible format

Before you reply you must:

  • check the identity of the requester
  • remove any data which does not relate to them
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content: You could be fined if you do not respond to the request or provide the information requested.
chunks.plain_content:
Respond to a data protection request
What you must do
You could be fined if you do not respond to the request or provide the information requested.

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content: You might not need to give all the personal information you have about someone if requested - for example, if it contains legal advice or relates to another person.
chunks.plain_content:
Respond to a data protection request
Exemptions
You might not need to give all the personal information you have about someone if requested - for example, if it contains legal advice or relates to another person.

heading_context: Respond to a data protection request
chunks.html_content: Find out more about how to respond to requests. For further advice, contact the Information Commissioners Office (ICO).
chunks.plain_content:
Respond to a data protection request
Further information
Find out more about how to respond to requests. For further advice, contact the Information Commissioners Office (ICO).
